  (E'Guenther', E'Delle', E'President', E'Ornametals Manufacturing, LLC', NULL, E'guenther@ornametals.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Decatur, Alabama, United States', E'United States', E'President/Vice President', E'C-Suite', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/guenther-huber-delle-37b48242', E'Ornametals™ fabricates architectural ornaments in copper and zinc. We can make anything... finials, leaderheads, dormers, cupolas, and decorative items such as molding & panels -- We are also specialists in the historic restoration field. Let us help with your next project. If you''re interested in becoming a distributor, purchasing our products, or looking for a restoration consultation, feel free to visit either message me or visit one of our websites, www.ornametals.com or www.copperworkscorps.com, for more information.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/ornametals-manufacturing-llc', E'Building Materials', E'Ornametals Manufacturing, LLC. Located in Cullman, Alabama, Ornametals Manufacturing began operations in mid-2008. Primarily focusing on “EuroGutterUSA”, green and sustainable European style half-round copper and zinc gutters and welded downspouts with a complete range of architectural sheet metal products. Ornametals manufactures its product line in a 27,000 square foot facility on state-of-the-art equipment, and is an industry leader in historical restoration, ornaments and provides design and consultation services to the architectural and construction community. For more information, contact Ornametals at (256) 255-0190.', E'[''construction/building materials'', ''copper and zinc gutters and downspouts'', ''historic restoration'', ''ornaments'', ''architectural sheet metal products'', ''folded-seam downspouts'', ''seamless-weld downspouts'', ''crimped elbows'', ''architectural ornaments'', ''copper gutters'', ''manufacturing'', ''wholesale'']', E'https://www.ornametals.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Cullman, Alabama, United States', E'Cullman', E'Alabama', E'United States', E'[''(256) 255-0190'', ''256-255-0190'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, E'https://www.facebook.com/pages/ornametals-manufacturing/443457032409686', E'https://www.twitter.com/ornametals', NULL, NULL, E'6783790'),
  (E'Jesse', E'Telaak', E'Principal', E'Blast Off Inc.', NULL, E'jtelaak@blastoffny.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Buffalo-Niagara Falls Area United States', E'United States', E'Senior', E'C-Suite', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jessetelaak', E'I have been in the coatings removal and re-application industry for over 9 years. We are able to provide a unique service that was not available in our area. Our coatings removal process is faster and safer than traditional methods. In addition to coatings removal services we provide sandblasting and painting for the industrial industry as well as heavy equipment refinishing , and others as well.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/blast-off-inc.', E'Consumer Services', E'We are a sandblasting and coatings provider. We blast and paint everything from large industrial bases, tanks, and pressure vessels down to car frames. We also provide finishing services for Stainless Steel items. We have been in business since 2005 providing our services to many industries in the Western New York area.', E'[''bead blasting'', ''surface preparation'', ''sand blasting'', ''soda blasting'', ''painting'', ''industrial painting'', ''manufacturing/engineering'', ''abrasive blasting'', ''painting services'', ''industrial coatings'', ''sandblasting'', ''automotive restoration'']', E'https://www.blastoffny.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Buffalo, NY, United States', E'Buffalo', E'New York', E'United States', E'[''716-691-7013'', ''716-568-7502'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, E'https://www.facebook.com/blastoffny', E'https://www.twitter.com/blastoffny', NULL, NULL, E'3673621'),
  (E'James', E'Jendusa', E'President', E'Forteco Framing Company', NULL, E'jim@fortecoframing.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Hartland, Wisconsin, United States', E'United States', E'President/Vice President', E'C-Suite', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jendusa', E'I’m a structural engineer, entrepreneur, and builder dedicated to creating resilient…', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/forteco-framing-company', E'Wholesale Building Materials', E'Forteco Framing Company sells and installs the FORTECO "Lightweight Composite Framing" system developed by Lightweight Structutes, LLC. The Forteco Floor and Wall framing is a unique composite building system for commercial, industrial, institutional, and residential structures. The patented system cleverly utilizes steel, concrete, and insulation as structural components for floor and wall framing. Advantages of floors and walls built using the FORTECO Lightweight Composite Framing (LCF) System include strength, rigidity, durability, mold, rot and insect resistance; sound attenuation, high R-values, thermal mass, suitability for in-floor radiant heating and the availability of decorative concrete finishes. FORTECO framing is a modular building system that can reduce construction costs, shorten construction time, while creating a super-insulated building offering an excellent platform for "Net Zero" construction using emerging green building technologies with extra LEED credits available..', E'[''construction'', ''tilt-up walls'', ''basement walls'', ''composite floor framing'', ''green building'', ''multi-story building'', ''floor framing'', ''wall framing'', ''precast wall panels'', ''steel joists'', ''steel studs'', ''lightweight composite framing'', ''light gauge steel'', ''concrete composite'', ''pre-manufactured'', ''pre-engineered'']', E'https://www.fortecoframing.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Hartland, WI, United States', E'Hartland', E'Wisconsin', E'United States', E'[''(262)369-3800'']', E'[''support@fortecoframing.com'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
  (E'Jack', E'Ruffino', E'President', E'Jack the Roofer Inc. (Arizona)', NULL, E'jack@jacktherooferaz.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Phoenix, Arizona, United States', E'United States', E'Specialist', E'Trades', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jack-ruffino-9875a578', E'Our company has over 24 years experience serving over 15,000 satisfied customers here in the valley; We are repair specialists and complete replacement professionals. Our staff has the knowledge and experience to know where these roofs fail as well as suggesting yearly maintenance helping to keep overall repairs to a minimum. At Jack the Roofer Inc., we are experts in various roof systems present here in the valley and neighboring areas. We will continue to strive to support our community in maintaining high standards of professionalism in all your roofing needs. We offer free estimates and free yearly inspections to all of our customers. Let''s Talk: Jack Ruffino jacktheroofer@cox.net 602-996-7443 http://jacktherooferaz.com', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/jack-the-roofer-inc-arizona-', E'Construction', E'Are you searching for a reliable, professional and ethical roof repair specialist in Phoenix and surrounding cities? If so – look no farther, as Jack the Roofer Inc. has an affordable roof repair and installation program to suit your needs. 

There are many reasons why you''d need to find a reliable roof repair expert, however it seems to always come up when you least expect it. Whether you have noticed a small leak in your roof after a huge thundershower, or you''ve seen some of your roof shingles sitting on your front lawn instead of on the roof where they belong, you can trust that Jack the Roofer has a solution for your particular roof issue. 

Our company is licensed, insured and bonded to work on virtually any structure, commercial or residential and has vast experience in getting the job done right and always within your price budget. From asphalt shingle roofs, to tile roofs and even space-age foam roof installation, we have the experience to take on virtually any roof project. And we would like the opportunity to work with you on any roof repair, inspection or replacement project you have. 

For more information about how Jack the Roofer can help you with any commercial or residential roof inspection, repair or installation job in Phoenix and beyond, contact us today by phone at 602-996-7443 or email: jacktheroofer@cox.net', E'[''construction/building materials'', ''roofing repair'', ''roofing installations'', ''roof maintenance'', ''written roof reports'', ''foam roofing & coating'', ''shingle roofs'', ''concrete & clay tile roofs'', ''sand cast tile roofng'', ''wood shake roofing'', ''modified roofing'', ''commercial'', ''tile roof installations'', ''residential'', ''flat roofing'', ''roofing'', ''industry: n/a'', ''construction'']', E'https://www.jacktherooferaz.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Phoenix, Arizona, United States', E'Phoenix', E'Arizona', E'United States', E'[''+1 602 996 7443'', ''602-996-7443'', ''(602) 975-3363'']', E'[''jack@jacktherooferaz.com'', ''jacktheroofer@cox.net'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, E'https://www.facebook.com/jacktherooferaz', E'https://www.twitter.com/jacktherooferaz', E'https://www.youtube.com/user/jacktherooferaz', NULL, NULL),
  (E'Ed', E'Deangelis', E'Owner', E'Bregenzer Brothers Company, Inc.', NULL, E'edeangelis@edacontractors.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Greater Philadelphia United States', E'United States', E'C-Level', E'C-Suite', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/edwarddeangelis', E'Edward DeAngelis founded EDA Contractors in 1999 after spending 11 years at Belcher Roofing Corporation. As a leader in the markets it serves, EDA Contractors provides unique benefits for its clients, partners, employees and community - and is proud to be recognized by six consecutive placements in the Philadelphia Inquirer’s Top Workplaces (2018-2023) and several honors as a NJ.com and USA Top Workplace. Under Ed''s steadfast leadership, EDA Contractors specializes in the exterior envelope of all commercial, institutional, and industrial buildings. EDA’s areas of expertise include architectural wall panels and accessories, roofing, masonry, waterproofing, air vapor barrier, green roofing systems, historical restoration, and specialty components. The company’s commitment to its high quality of work is backed by the industry-leading EDA Envelope Warranty, a 10-year watertight guarantee. In addition to EDA’s commitment to providing customers with services that represent their pride in who they are and what they provide, the EDA Team, under the leadership of Ed, is dedicated to self-improvement that extends beyond the services offered and into the lives of all who make contact with them. EDA fosters a positive workplace and culture and is dedicated to personal and professional development, including mental health and wellness, physical and psychological safety, and emotional intelligence. Ed’s innovative personality has allowed EDA Contractors, Inc. to become a leader in its industry. Under his tutelage, EDA Contractors, Inc. started as a roofing contractor exclusively but has grown into a complete exterior envelope contractor. Always looking for another challenge, Ed has continually provided his customers with knowledgeable and qualified employees that share his unique vision. EDA Contractors, Inc. has been recognized for the past three straight years in the top five as a Top Workplace in Philadelphia by the Philadelphia Inquirer. Ed holds a Bachelor of Science in Business Management from Saint Joseph''s University. Additionally, Ed has been recognized for his professional and charitable work: 2017 Turnings Points "Person of the Year" 2018 Top Leadership Award - Mid-Size Company - Philly.com Top Work Places 2019 Top Company Direction Award - Mid-Size Company – Philadelphia Inquirer Top Work Places 2020 Top Leadership Award - Mid-Size Company – Philadelphia Inquirer Top Work Places', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/bregenzer-brothers', E'Construction', E'Bregenzer Brothers, Inc. is a third-generation family-owned and operated specialty slate and copper roofing and contracting firm based in Central New Jersey. We are a small company known for our artisanal skills and attention to detail, yet with the resources and capabilities to tackle even the largest jobs.', E'[''construction/building materials'', ''slate roofing'', ''copper roofing'', ''masonry'', ''consulting'', ''copper gutters'', ''restoration'', ''slate roofs'', ''leader heads'', ''installation'']', E'https://www.bregenzerbrothers.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Ewing, New Jersey, United States', E'Ewing', E'New Jersey', E'United States', E'[''215-638-3500'']', NULL, E'[''well'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, E'https://www.facebook.com/edacontractorsinc', NULL, NULL, E'https://www.instagram.com/edacontractors', NULL),
  (E'Michael', E'Warkentien', E'Owner', E'A1 Window Tinting', NULL, E'michaelw@a1windowtint.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Lees Summit, Missouri, United States', E'United States', E'Owner', E'C-Suite', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/mwarkentien', E'I am excited about my career and my abilities to help others succeed in life. I learned several years ago that by helping others achieve their goals, I was the one reaping the benefits. When you treat others the way you want to be treated and when you help others achieve what they want in life, the road to success is shortened. My entire career has been built around the fast pace and highly complex manufacturing environment. I have performed a variety of functions from entry-level positions to General Manager of multi-national operations. My ability to interpret technical requirements in conjunction with administrative, commercial and people skills is the primary reason for my success. During my career, ten years have been spent working overseas on three different assignments. My sensitivity towards globalization and different cultures has been enhanced through my knowledge of the Portuguese language, which I acquired while living in Brazil through my high school years. I have a diverse background in plastics manufacturing/technology, project management, strategic planning, complex environments and cultural integration with special emphasis in guiding teams through change. I am anxious to help others improve their operations in Latin America by incorporating the best R&amp;D Leverage has to offer. R&amp;D Leverage is one of the best kept secrets in South America. Their integrated approach from development of concepts through product and production analyses combined with state of the art mold manufacturing and after market support makes them the Global leader in their field. R&amp;D Leverage''s products and services sell themselves, my task is to demonstrate how they can best service the market and your company.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/a1-window-tinting-llc', E'Consumer Services', E'A1 Window Tinting LLC, provides superior solar window film products that offer the highest energy saving solutions available. We continuasly strive to create comfortable homes and buildings while improving the global environment. In addition to our automotive, residential and commercial tinting solutions we expanded our product offerings to include security and safety films. This innovative product delivers a new standard of protection for our customers, their families and property. We care deeply about our customer’s satisfaction with both our service and products we provide. Our employees take great care and pride in our efforts to be trustworthy and respectful throughout our entire relationship with each client. We work to always have 100% customer satisfaction.', E'[''window tinting'', ''sales@a1windowtint.com'', ''commercial'', ''automotive'', ''energy-saving solutions'', ''residential'']', E'https://www.a1windowtint.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Olathe, Kansas, United States', E'Olathe', E'Kansas', E'United States', E'[''913-829-5500'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
