  (E'Michael', E'Caruso', E'Advisory Board Member', E'Concrete Exchange', NULL, E'mike@concreteexchange.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'United States', E'United States', E'Specialist', E'Consulting', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/macaruso', E'With deep experience in strategy and innovation, I embrace ambiguity and thrive on creating something truly terrific with my team and clients. I leverage my skills in creative approaches, problem solving, and transformation to crystalize multi-year plans, optimize value realization, and accelerate the execution of investments. Throughout my career, I have enjoyed various innovation and leadership positions in supply chain, technology, and start-up domains. I have implemented new programs that sense disruption, mitigate risk, and identify new opportunities. I am also an advisory board member and an investor in two diverse and exciting ventures. I am grateful for each and every challenge and look forward to the next.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cheng-concrete-llc', E'Wholesale Building Materials', E'Headquartered in Concord, CA, Concrete Exchange operates strategically located fulfillment centers on both the West and East Coasts, including a facility in Dade City, FL. Through a dynamic partnership with Amazon''s vast distribution network, we guarantee swift and efficient delivery of products to customers throughout the US, precisely meeting their demands.

