  (E'Brandy', E'Littrell', E'Director of Marketing', E'Stala Integrated Assemblies', NULL, E'brandy.littrell@stalaframing.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Louisville, Kentucky, United States', E'United States', E'Specialist', E'Operations', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/brandy-littrell-ahc-42791114', E'With a background in retail sales, I have fifteen years in the commercial construction industry as an estimator and part of the sales team at the Atlas Companies. I have a wide range of product knowledge that covers six divisions of work with most of my experience/projects falling into the education and healthcare fields. In addition to estimating and sales functions, I also work extremely hard at examining challenges that may arise in order to better contain costs for our clients and end users on all projects. Since becoming a part of the Atlas team I have obtained my BA from McKendree University and my MBA from University of the Cumberlands. I am also an Architectural Hardware Consultant (AHC).', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/stala-integrated-assemblies', E'Building Materials', E'The Stala story began in 2006. A representative for an ICF company asked Andy Keith for help in creating a commercial-grade solution to door and window openings in ICF buildings. Keith specialized in door and window frames for commercial construction at The Atlas Companies. Along with Jonathan Keith and James Essex, Keith proceeded in designing steel frames that ICF block could be stacked around, and which would interlock with the concrete walls. They named these custom-designed steel framing assemblies “Stala”, and they have now placed thousands of them on hundreds of jobsites. The designers hold two US patents for design and utility with the US Patent Office. Stala frames are now a premiere product in commercial ICF construction, preferred by Owners for their contribution to energy efficiency, by Architects for their coordination with multiple trades and superior quality, and by Contractors for the capacity to speed construction time.', E'[''environmental services'', ''environmental sustainability'', ''são paulo'', ''waste disposal'', ''construction waste'', ''soil cleaning'']', E'https://www.stalaframing.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Louisville, Kentucky, United States', E'Louisville', E'Kentucky', E'United States', E'[''1-502-779-2118'', ''502-526-6127'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, E'https://www.facebook.com/pages/stala-integrated-framing-assemblies-llc/145863295488', NULL, E'https://www.youtube.com/channel/ucrjm5pcf7-2jnwlbqnbga8a', NULL, NULL),
