  (E'Jana', E'Williams', E'Plumbing Dispatch Manager', E'Cool Air Mechanical - Atlanta', NULL, E'jwilliams@770coolair.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Dallas, Georgia, United States', E'United States', NULL, NULL, E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/jana-williams-826bab331', E'As a female professional in the plumbing industry—a field traditionally dominated by men—I have not only built a successful career but have also overcome the challenges that come with breaking barriers. Starting as a Customer Service Representative, I worked my way up to Plumbing Dispatch Manager, gaining firsthand experience in both customer relations and service operations. This journey has strengthened my resilience, deepened my expertise, and fueled my passion for leadership in the trades. In my current role, I excel at optimizing service operations, ensuring technicians are dispatched efficiently, and maintaining a seamless customer experience. I thrive in fast-paced environments where problem-solving, team coordination, and strategic planning are key to success. Beyond dispatch and operations, I am a skilled Journeyman Plumber actively working toward my Master Plumber License, merging hands-on expertise with leadership in service management. One of my greatest passions is advocating for more women to enter and thrive in the plumbing industry. Having faced and overcome adversity, I am committed to fostering an inclusive environment where women feel empowered to build lasting careers in the trades. My ultimate goal is to continue making an impact—both through my own growth and by supporting the next generation of skilled tradeswomen. I welcome opportunities to connect with like-minded professionals, industry leaders, and aspiring tradespeople to share insights, collaborate, and continue driving change in this evolving field. Let’s connect!', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cool-air-mechanical---atlanta', E'Utilities', E'Cool Air Mechanical offers air conditioning, heati