  (E'Debra', E'Eagle', E'General Manager', E'Hestan Vineyards', NULL, E'debra@hestan.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Sonoma, California, United States', E'United States', E'Manager', E'C-Suite', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/debra-eagle-0570a733', NULL, E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/hestan-vineyards', E'Wine & Spirits', E'Hestan Vineyards is a 41-acre vineyard located on Napa Valley''s eastern slopes at the base of Okell Hill. Individually farmed blocks planted to all five Bordeaux varietals--Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot, Petit Verdot, Cabernet Franc and Malbec--blanket the rolling hills overlooking the vineyard''s 11-acre pond.

Consulting winemaker Mark Herold began working with the Hestan estate in 2002, creating his hallmark opulent wines with the 2002 Hestan Cabernet Sauvignon and the 2002 Meyer Cabernet Sauvignon. Both were a critical success.

In 2005, winemaker Jeff Gaffner began the Stephanie project to showcase all five of the Bordeaux varietals planted at the estate. He produces a Stephane Red Wine, (Bordeaux blend) , Merlot and Cabernet Sauvignon from the property.

This harvest (2009) Thomas Rivers Brown is taking over production of the Hestan wines from Herold. Considered one of the rising stars of Napa Valley, Thomas made history as the youngest winemaker to receive two perfect 100 point scores from Robert Parker.

Hestan Vineyards owner Stanley Cheng notes, "We feel very excited and privileged to have winemakers of such accomplishment interpret our vineyard''s terroir in such wonderfully expressive styles. We think our entire portfolio of wines--Hestan, Meyer and Stephanie--will continue to improve with each vintage."', E'[''food & beverage'', ''excellent bordeaux varietal wines'', ''cooking'', ''home services'', ''manufacturing'', ''service industry'', ''culinary innovation'', ''restaurants'', ''home'', ''cookware'', ''vineyards'']', E'https://www.hestan.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Yountville, California, United States', E'Yountville', E'California', E'United States', E'[''+1 714 869 2393'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, E'https://www.facebook.com/hestanhome', E'https://www.twitter.com/hestanvineyards', NULL, E'https://www.instagram.com/hestancue', NULL),
  (E'Ever', E'Chacon', E'Product Manager', E'Anchor Point Roofing', NULL, E'ever@anchorpointroofing.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Greater Chicago Area United States', E'United States', E'Manager', E'Product', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/ever-chacon-699a83156', E'I’ve always been hands-on and driven to build—whether it’s a house, a team, or a business.

I got my start in construction back in high school, and since then, I’ve worked in various areas, such as HUD projects, renovations, fix-and-flips, REOs, and property preservation. Over the years, I’ve learned how to manage crews, solve problems on the fly, and keep projects moving forward—no matter how tough the challenge.

What I enjoy most about this work is that there’s always something new to learn and improve. The construction world doesn’t sit still and is constantly evolving.

These days, I’m focused on growing, taking on new projects, and meeting people who are also working hard to build something of their own. I’m always open to good conversations, fresh ideas, and new opportunities.

Let’s connect—I’d love to hear what you’re working on!', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/anchor-point-roofing', E'Construction', E'𝗔𝗻𝗰𝗵𝗼𝗿 𝗣𝗼𝗶𝗻𝘁 𝗥𝗼𝗼𝗳𝗶𝗻𝗴 | 𝗖𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗮𝗴𝗼

Replacing a roof shouldn’t feel uncertain.

At 𝗔𝗻𝗰𝗵𝗼𝗿 𝗣𝗼𝗶𝗻𝘁 𝗥𝗼𝗼𝗳𝗶𝗻𝗴, we help 𝗖𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗮𝗴𝗼-𝗮𝗿𝗲𝗮 𝗵𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗼𝘄𝗻𝗲𝗿𝘀 make confident, informed decisions about full roof replacement—especially when insurance, storm damage, or aging systems are involved.

We don’t lead with price.
We lead with 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗰𝗲𝘀𝘀, 𝗱𝗼𝗰𝘂𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻, 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗰𝗹𝗮𝗿𝗶𝘁𝘆.

Our work is built for homeowners who value:
• A clear assessment before committing
• Proper documentation for insurance decisions
• Quality materials installed the right way
• Communication they don’t have to chase
• A roof that protects their home for decades—not just the next storm

𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗪𝗲 𝗦𝗽𝗲𝗰𝗶𝗮𝗹𝗶𝘇𝗲 𝗜𝗻
• Full residential roof replacement
• Storm & hail damage assessments
• High-value homes and complex roofs
• Clean, professional installs with no shortcuts

From the first inspection to final cleanup, our team follows a 𝘀𝘁𝗿𝘂𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲𝗱, 𝘁𝗿𝗮𝗻𝘀𝗽𝗮𝗿𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗰𝗲𝘀𝘀 designed to eliminate guesswork and protect your investment.

If you’re a homeowner who wants it done **𝗼𝗻𝗰𝗲—𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗱𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗿𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁**, Anchor Point Roofing is built for you.

📍 Serving Chicago and surrounding suburbs
📩 Schedule a roof assessment via our website or connect with us here on LinkedIn

