  (E'Mirjana', E'Kokinis', E'VP of Finance & Operations', E'StaticWorx, Inc', NULL, E'mirjana.kokinis@staticworx.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'South Burlington, Vermont, United States', E'United States', E'Specialist', E'Finance & Accounting', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/mirjana-miki-kokinis-4921147b', E'Over a 16 of finance and accounting proficiency has honed my expertise in cash optimization and process improvement within the consumer packaged goods domain, and the last 6 years in the electronics/construction sector prominently as Controller at Staticworx, Inc. My tenure has been marked by spearheading initiatives in merchant services and operations optimization, which have been pivotal in driving our organizational growth.

At the heart of my professional journey lies a commitment to enhancing customer and vendor relations through meticulous credit and cash management. The integration of Six Sigma methodologies into our financial forecasting and analysis has empowered our team to achieve operational excellence and substantial efficiency gains, ensuring maximum returns and robust financial health for Staticworx, Inc.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/staticworx', E'Wholesale Building Materials', E'StaticWorx provides high-performance static-control flooring systems engineered for mission-critical environments. Our GroundSafe® ESD flooring platforms prevent random electrostatic discharge (ESD) events in electronics manufacturing, SMT facilities, cleanrooms, labs, data centers, and any operation working with sensitive or high-speed electronic components.

Every solution begins with an assessment of your environment, risks, and performance thresholds. From there, we design a complete system that includes the optimal flooring material along with the correct installation method, grounding strategy, footwear protocols, seating, mobile carts, and other elements that influence charge generation and dissipation.

Our portfolio supports a wide range of technical and operational requirements:
– ShadowFX® SDT carpet tile
– AmeriWorx™ conductive and static-dissipative vinyl tile
– Eclipse™ EC and Eclipse Plus™ conductive rubber
– GroundWorx™ ESD epoxy and coatings
– GroundLock™ Extreme interlocking tile

Our agile team of ESD-control specialists supports architects, designers, engineers, contractors, and facilities managers with deep technical knowledge and real-world insight. We collaborate closely with teams in electronics manufacturing, aerospace, cleanrooms, government, healthcare, and advanced technology to ensure alignment with ANSI/ESD S20.20 and operational requirements.

All StaticWorx GroundSafe® floors are backed by a lifetime warranty for static control. After installation, we continue to support clients through testing, verification, and system optimization.

