  (E'Bill', E'Ferrin', E'Estimator--PM', E'Wheeler Air Conditioning', NULL, E'billf@wheelerair.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Scottsdale, Arizona, United States', E'United States', E'Manager', E'Project Management', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/bferrin', E'I grew up working after school and summers in the family A/C business and learned it pretty well. My Dad pulled out of the company in the mid 90''s and my two brothers and I continued to run company for many years. Partnerships don''t last forever and I was bought out in 2007. Real Estate was logical, I had done the schooling and received a license earlier that year and I knew I could make it work. So I put my head down and went to work. I specialized in working with bank properties, distressed properties and mostly dealt with investors. My knack for finding the deals brought many other clients my way and I didn''t have to do a lot of advertising to stay busy. I started my own brokerage in 2010 and will keep it going as long as my investors keep using my services. My wife Julie is also a real estate agent and runs a good portion of that. I decided earlier this year that I wanted to do more than just real estate. It''s hard to build more than a job in real estate no matter how hard you work. Jack Bennett one of the owners of Bennett and Porter has been a friend of mine for several years, he encouraged the switch and has helped me get started. My back ground in construction and real estate has helped me to understand the needs of small businesses and made it easy to talk to business owners. Jack and the others working here have developed some great relationships and programs and we have been able to help most of those we meet with to figure out the correct coverage they need as well as find them the best price on that coverage.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/wheeler-air-conditioning', E'Business Supplies & Equipment', NULL, E'[''home services'', ''air conditioning repair'', ''expert s