  (E'Brian', E'Deska', E'Owner', E'DESKA', NULL, E'brian@deskaservices.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'New Alexandria, Virginia, United States', E'United States', E'Owner', E'C-Suite', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/brian-e-deska-p-e-97921813', NULL, E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/deska-services-llc', E'Construction', E'Deska Services is a licensed professional engineering, specialty structural contractor, and general service contracting company. Our range of services varies from structural engineering design, structural repair, foundation underpinning, and waterproofing. 

Deska Services staff includes licensed structural engineers, class A building technical, commercial, and residential contractors, construction managers, and skilled tradesmen with numerous specialty certifications. We pride ourselves on our diverse range of in-house skills compared to most general or specialty contractors. When necessary, we do have a select group of affiliate subcontractors for super specialized skillsets to meet contract requirements. 

Deska Services culture embraces that the estimated value of the project should equal or exceed the final project cost and we consistently are able to come in at or under budget on 92% of our projects. 

Why Deska Services?

At Deska Services, we’ve made a name for ourselves through our “we do what we say we’re going to do” culture and our dedication to our strict quality control procedures and training. Our project management approach is based on our clients’ vision and end goals depending on their unique situation and timeline. Our responsiveness and convenience to work with is second to none, along with our positive attitudes guided by our culture, make getting the project done right – Every Time, with minimal effort from our clients and partners. 

We strive to always provide prompt and clear communication and to always keep our clients informed on a “real-time” basis. In order to provide the optimal service and solution, Deska Services always has professionally licensed engineers on staff for technical and field support to make sure the project is performed correctly.', E'[''construction/building materials'', ''drainage improvements'', ''basement waterproofing'', ''waterproofing'', ''crawl space repair'', ''foundation repair'', ''engineering'', ''exterior installations and coatings'', ''waterproofing & drainage solutions'', ''foundation repair & settlement solutions'', ''tenant turnovers'', ''structural repairs'', ''restoration'', ''civil engineering'', ''construction'', ''home renovation'']', E'https://www.deskaservices.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Alexandria, Virginia, United States', E'Alexandria', E'Virginia', E'United States', E'[''(703) 552-8201'', ''703-826-0604'', ''+1-703-552-8201'', ''(240) 630-3290'', ''240-630-3290'', ''703-665-1456'', ''703-552-8201'']', E'[''info@deskaservices.com'']', E'[''autocad'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, E'https://www.facebook.com/deskaservices', E'https://www.twitter.com/deskaservices', NULL, NULL, NULL),
  (E'Cathy', E'George', E'VP Finance', E'Redux', NULL, E'cathy.george@redux.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Fishers, Indiana, United States', E'United States', E'President/Vice President', E'Finance & Accounting', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/cathy-george', E'Experienced CPA with a demonstrated history of working in the consumer services industry. Led accounting department including tax and forward/reverse logistics. Experience with debt refinancing; due diligence; quarterly compliance and working with all levels across the organizations, including C-level and Board of Directors . Skilled in Monthly financial analysis and reserve reporting.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/get-redux', E'Consumer Services', E'Redux, a patented drying technology that removes 100% of the liquid from wet electronics if you encounter a spill, can save you time, money, and salvage your data.

Founded by Reuben Zielinski and Joel Trusty in Indianapolis in 2013, Redux uses their patented technique to remove moisture from liquid-damaged cell phones, cameras, tablets, MP3 players and other devices, and returns them to working condition.

The idea for Redux came when Trusty’s wife subjected her cell phone to a full cycle in the washing machine and was devastated that not only was the phone ruined, but all the data, contact information, photos and videos were lost. With a background in manufacturing, Trusty thought of a concept for how to save his wife’s phone and knew that his friend and neighbor, Zielinski, an ex-IBM employee, had the equipment to put it into practice. Together, they fixed the phone, and within one week created the first Redux model.

Currently, Redux is available at over 2000 wireless retail stores throughout the U.S. For more information, visit the Redux website.', E'[''electrical services'', ''mobile phone repair and electronics repair'', ''technology'', ''consumer-electronics'', ''consumer-products-services'', ''industrial and public works'', ''data centers'', ''expert electricians'', ''industrial electrical services'', ''ediscovery'', ''internet'', ''social media'', ''tv'']', E'https://www.redux.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Fishers, Indiana, United States', E'Fishers', E'Indiana', E'United States', E'[''844.733.8948'']', E'[''support@redux.com'', ''inquiries@redux.com'']', E'[''redux'', ''quickbooks online'', ''salesforce'', ''quickbooks'', ''impact'']', E'Venture Round', NULL, E'2012-12-10', E'https://www.facebook.com/getredux', E'https://www.twitter.com/getredux', NULL, NULL, E'7508214'),
