  (E'Josh', E'Borner', E'Outside Sales Rep', E'Foss Exteriors LLC', NULL, E'josh@fossexteriors.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Monticello, Minnesota, United States', E'United States', E'Owner', E'C-Suite', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/josh-borner-2513a614', E'I am Josh Borner; I sell and facilitate exterior renovations. I’ve been in the construction business for over 20 years. I not only specialize in helping my clients restore their property after sustaining damage as a result of catastrophic weather events, I am especially eager to collaborate on renewing a home’s character by way of remodeling. My services are in high demand, by both homeowners, and property managers alike. I bring both the experience of an installer, as well as the expertise of a project manager. I guide my clients throughout the entire process by offering advice on design, as well as educating them on quality products and proper installation. I wake up every day excited to get to work. I really love what I do, and look forward to every new opportunity.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/foss-exteriors-llc', E'Construction', E'Insurance Claims, Roofing, Siding, Windows & Appraisals. Trevor Foss has been working on the exteriors of Twin Cities homes for more than 25 years. He started out helping his father with the work, but was quickly recruited by additional customers. He’s run his own business almost the entire time. Foss has the expertise to work on a wide variety of houses, including small city homes, townhouses and condominiums, and multi-million dollar mansions. 
He graduated from Minnesota State University-Mankato in 1992 with a degree in construction management and a minor in both accounting and computer science. He continues to keep his skills current by regularly attending vocational classes, continuing education courses and various seminars.
One of the things that helps us set ourselves apart from the rest in this competitive home improvement market is our commitment to embracing the newest technologies available to stay connected with our onsite crews and our customers.
Being on top of changing weather conditions is critical when working on your roof, siding or windows. Our crews carry smartphones to help in monitoring weather and communicate via text message and email with the office for the most efficient scheduling and planning on each job.
