  (E'Emily', E'Jacks', E'Operations Support Manager', E'Advantage Tile and Grout Cleaning', NULL, E'emily@advantagetile.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Denver Metropolitan Area United States', E'United States', E'Manager', E'Operations', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/emilybaker', E'After spending my childhood in Wichita, KS I attended Rockhurst University in Kansas City where I graduated with a degree in Business Management. Upon graduating, I made my way in the real estate business where I developed a passion for customer service and a drive to help my clients make their dreams come true. After conquering real estate, I turned my sights on the service industry as a sales manager for a multi-venue property in downtown Kansas City. It was here that my love of event planning blossomed and I mastered the art of multi-tasking. In my free time, I love spending time with my two poodles and enjoying the outdoors. Whether it is hiking, biking or snowboarding, I love spending time enjoying beautiful Colorado. I''m also an avid supporter in the fight against breast cancer and devote much of my time volunteering for organizations that promote Breast Cancer early screening, education and awareness.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/advantage-tile-and-grout-cleaning', E'Consumer Services', NULL, E'[''contact centre solutions'', ''digital transformation'', ''technology'', ''customer experiences'', ''agent experiences'']', E'https://www.advantagetile.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Denver, Colorado, United States', E'Denver', E'Colorado', E'United States', E'[''(303) 439-8453'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, E'https://www.facebook.com/people/advantage-tile-grout-cleaning/100068469234547', NULL, NULL, E'https://www.instagram.com/advantagetileco', E'12553522'),
  (E'Clay', E'Baldwin', E'Outside Sales Representative', E'Christian Brothers Roofing & Contracting', NULL, E'clay@christianbroroofing.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Louisville, Kentucky, United States', E'United States', E'Specialist', E'Sales', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/claybaldwinrealtor', E'Clay’s love for his community and the city of Louisville run deep. He holds his personal work ethic, tenacious sense of drive, and commitment to integrity, at the highest of standards. His authentic and genuine style of communication is truly an asset to clients. Having spent his early career fine-tuning the ability to foster and nurture relationships; he brings to Semonin a host of connections, which have allowed him to find great success in the real estate industry. He strives for nothing more than to provide clients with catered direction in making sound investments. Clay earned his license, to work alongside his wife, Lauren. Their hope is that as a team, they can strengthen every aspect of the buying/selling process, in pursuit of seamless transactions. Aside from professional endeavors, he takes every opportunity to spend quality time with his wife and daughter; tighten up his golf game; cheer on the Louisville Cardinals and Chicago Cubs; and keep friends and family belly-laughing.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/christian-brothers-roofing-%26-contracting', E'Construction', E'Christian Brothers Roofing was incorporated in 1997 by Gary Jenkens in an effort to create a roofing company that genuinely cares about customers, understands the importance of high-quality work and provides a place that the owner’s family and employees could be proud to work for. With over 19 years of experience in serving the Louisville metro area, we have installed over 9,000 roofs.

At Christian Brothers Roofing, we distinguish ourselves from the competition by offering a no-hassle approach to sales. We don’t work on commission, which takes the pressure off our employees and customers, allowing us to focus on providing superior service. Our goal is to make the entire roofing process as easy and efficient as possible so we can continue to satisfy every single customer.

