  (E'Stuart', E'Urban', E'Owner/Certified Dryer Exhaust Technician', E'LintFree Dryer Vent Cleaning, LLC', NULL, E'stuart@lintfreedryervents.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Aurora, Colorado, United States', E'United States', E'Specialist', E'Trades', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/stuartjurban', E'I am "A jack of all trades and a master of none, but oftentimes better than a master of one". Throughout my life I have worked hard were ever I worked and played. Moving around has always been the theme my life. Having different jobs have given me a wide expanse of experiences. Even though the positions I held varied, there had been a constant variable with them all, building relationships. Whether it was being a swim coach, sailing school manager a children''s shoe sales person or a banker. I have done a lot more than what I have mentioned with the same common theme, helping people realize their potential. In 2010 while trying to figure out the next move I would make in my everlasting search for the perfect job, by the way, there isn''t one, I wanted to started a business that would last and be successful. LintFree Dryer Vent, LLC is my baby. I am the owner/operator for 14 year. I have and do love my job, however, there is a time in which one, especially me, has to ask is it time for a new adventure. With more and more people getting into this industry, it has become increasingly hard to keep the market share that I used to have. So I have decided to start looking for something relatively new. People have asked me what I am looking for. Well, I am looking for a position that is interesting, in a industry that I am familiar with, banking, loan originating, perhaps. should be challenging, where there are people involved and that I could make a decent salary doing. Is there a position that would fit me, with my diverse history? I say, there is. I am open to the many possibilities that are out there.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/lintfree-dryer-vent-cleaning-llc', E'Consumer Services', E'Clogged up dryer vents can lead to dryer fires. LintFree Dryer Vent Cleaning service can professionally clean your dryer vents quickly, efficiently and affordably. 

While dryer lint traps typically catch about 60% of clothing lint, the other 40% ends up in the dryer vent system. Over time, it builds up in areas not seen by the naked eye. Accumulated lint in the dryer vent system, combined with very hot air trying to get through the system, could result in unexpected and hard-to-find fires. Don’t be one of 18,000 people to experience a dryer vent fire this year! 

Serving the Denver metro area, LintFree Dryer Vent Cleaning is owned and operated by Stuart Urban, a Certified Dryer Exhaust Technician. Certified through the Chimney Safety Institute of America, Stuart has been servicing area dryer vents since 2010, checking for problems before doing any work, providing upfront pricing so you know exactly what you’re paying for, and asking if you’re completely satisfied before leaving. Stuart takes dryer vent cleaning seriously and is ready to get the job done for you.', E'[''home services'', ''dryer vent cleaning'', ''customer service'', ''vent repair and replace'', ''transition duct repair'', ''dryer lint cleanout'', ''residential'', ''spas'', ''salons'', ''fitness centers'']', E'https://www.dryerventcleaningco.com', E'1 employee', NULL, E'Aurora, CO, United States', E'Aurora', E'Colorado', E'United States', E'[''(720) 951-1834'']', NULL, E'[''electric'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, E'https://www.facebook.com/pages/lintfree-dryer-vent-cleaning-llc/331966130182777', E'https://www.twitter.com/lintfreedryers', NULL, NULL, E'3934142'),
