  (E'Thomas', E'Fields', E'Special Project Manager', E'TriVAN Roofing', NULL, E'thomas@trivanroofing.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'San Antonio, Texas, United States', E'United States', E'Manager', E'Project Management', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/thomas-fields-7378a62bb', NULL, E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/trivan-roofing-%26-construction', E'Construction', E'Sherry and Dave Custable formed TriVAN in 2001 with the goal of providing a stable future for their three children. Emphasis on family is deeply rooted in TriVAN''s history and is evidenced by the company name itself, Tri meaning three (Vanessa, Anthony, Nicholette). Our purpose is to operate as a family business that adds honesty and integrity to an industry sorely lacking in both. We aim to be more than just a faceless corporation fixated on the bottom line; we understand that roofing is about protection and we provide peace of mind by only working with the best materials and professionals. To that end we have persistently sought self improvement. TriVAN is licensed by the Roofing Contractors Association of Texas (RCAT) and Endorsed by the CIB for Commercial Roofing in Oklahoma. TriVAN has established itself as a commercial Elite Certified Contractor with Duro-Last PVC roof systems, and as a residential GAF Shingle Manufacturer Master Elite (License #ME21251). The emphasis on customer safety and satisfaction from every single one of our committed team members is the reason why TriVAN has an A+ rating with the Better Business Bureau. 98% of our multi-million dollar revenue base is from customer referrals, which we believe to be representative of our mission. 

Please contact us today for a free inspection or to answer any of your roofing questions. 

