  (E'Renato', E'Briones', E'Ecommerce Analyst', E'Advanced Component Services', NULL, E'rbriones@acsend2end.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Renton, Washington, United States', E'United States', E'Specialist', E'Research', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/renato-briones-9aa570187', E'Customer-oriented Account Manager and graduate in Business Management. Self-motivated and enthusiastic. Highly interested on sales, entrepreneurship, digital marketing and leadership. Adaptive and deadline-oriented with the ability to execute multiple projects in high stress environments. Advanced command of Spanish and Microsoft Excel.', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/advanced-component-services', E'Wholesale', E'Started in 2006, Advanced Component Services (ACS) is a contract manufacturer, commercial component distributor, e-commerce third party seller and, since 2014, an Amazon Vendor. ACS operates its main office and distribution center in the Seattle area and has support offices and warehouses in China and England.

Commercial Division

From its inception, ACS has operated as a contract manufacturer and commercial distributor primarily focused on developing and selling components used in commercial food service equipment, beverage equipment and lighting.

ACS has manufactured over 4,000 different products for its commercial customers. We directly or indirectly supply components to companies operating supermarkets, c-stores, bakeries, coffee shops, restaurants, office coffee service businesses and other types of establishments.

In addition to the products manufactured by our company, we maintain a large inventory of popular components from companies such as Robertshaw, Parker, Southco, Oetiker and several other fully stocked lines.

ACS is constantly looking for new products to manufacture for our existing and new commercial customers.

E-Commerce Division

In 2014, ACS launched an e-commerce division as part of a strategic initiative to create new revenue streams for its products. The e-commerce division has been very successful and has generated triple-digit growth since its creation. At the end of its fourth year, the e-commerce division was actively marketing and selling tens of thousands of products through a flow of up to 20,000 orders each month.

To support its e-commerce division’s growth, ACS is actively seeking new partnerships with component manufacturers and authorized distribution companies to purchase as many new products as possible to add to its product offering.

The e-commerce division’s products are sold through all the major marketplaces and standalone websites.', E'[''industrial services'', ''engineering'', ''industrial companies'', ''global design'', ''sourcing solutions'', ''commercial food service industry'', ''industrial manufacturing'', ''manufacturing'', ''plastics and rubber manufacturing'']', E'https://www.acsend2end.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Issaquah, Washington, United States', E'Issaquah', E'Washington', E'United States', E'[''1 (425) 363-2959'']', E'[''solutions@acsend2end.com'']', E'[''google sheets'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
