  (E'Michael', E'Reed', E'Technical Specialist', E'Master Painters Institute', NULL, E'michael.reed@mpi.net', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Springdale, Pennsylvania, United States', E'United States', E'Specialist', E'Engineering and Technical', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-reed-7b9a021b1', NULL, E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/master-painters-institute', E'Consumer Services', E'An Institute dedicated to the establishment of quality standards and quality assurance in the painting and coatings application Industry. 

The company aim is to ''Elevate the paint and coatings Industry through standards, guides and training'' 

Standards: MPI sets paint and coatings standards, then tests the products at the request on the manufacturers to ensure they meet the quality standards required by the industry. The MPI APL (Approved Product List) is vital for obtaining information on quality coatings and coating systems. 

The Master Painters Institute website (www.mpi.net) includes information for professional coating specifiers, architects, designers, property managers, painters and applicators. Featured are ''Caution Notes'' for the industry, which are explanations of coatings and substrate failures and the importance of standards. 

