  (E'Brett', E'Stratton', E'Customer Service Representative', E'Concrete Exchange', NULL, E'brett.stratton@concreteexchange.com', E'good', E'ok', E'99%', E'A-Leads', NULL, NULL, E'Walnut Creek, California, United States', E'United States', E'Specialist', E'Customer Service', E'https://www.linkedin.com/in/brett-stratton-933b7b31', E'I like to keep things light around the office, yet I am able to work under pressure. My belief is friends in the workplace is what keeps morale and productivity high. Because of the Air Force, I''m very easy-going in general attitude and adaptable about whatever last-minute project or situation may arise. As a result, I can stay flexible since nothing stays the same on the job. My work speaks for itself: Every customer I have dealt with enjoys that I helped them and treated them like a person and every team member comes to me for aid because I''m a hands-on teacher and walk the talk with my open door policy. Don''t let my silly personality fool you! I give whatever company I work for 100% and NOTHING less. Due to my military experience, I have been trained to do anything and everything at maximum output with the highest quality result possible. I have excellent people skills and am able to work with tense situations. A caring ear goes a long way to avoid escalation of issues that don''t need to be escalated in the first place. This includes both customers and team members. Because I''ve hit my peak as a customer support agent, I''d love to further my computer knowledge working in any computer-related industry, ideally continuing as a data analyst. I''m always eager to expand my knowledge and increase my skills. Learning new things is a fun challenge for me and I actually get really excited and motivated when I get to do something new or particularly challenging that others don''t wanna do. Some people need coffee, I need a something interesting to do! I''m looking for something remote because of many reasons (I have cats, my sister has babies and needs a baby sitter, my parents are elderly...) and it''s easier for me to be nearby in case something happens. My passion is in video games and I don''t make that a secret. I dream of making my own indie video game and I already have a demo out that''s constantly evolving and growing. I''m also a novel writer on Wattpad in my free time and I have multiple stories in the process of being created. Overall, writing is a hobby of mine and whether be it in games or books, I LOVE anything with a great story. If there''s anything you want to know, don''t hesitate to reach out. I''m an open book and not afraid to answer questions!', E'https://www.linkedin.com/company/cheng-concrete-llc', E'Wholesale Building Materials', E'Headquartered in Concord, CA, Concrete Exchange operates strategically located fulfillment centers on both the West and East Coasts, including a facility in Dade City, FL. Through a dynamic partnership with Amazon''s vast distribution network, we guarantee swift and efficient delivery of products to customers throughout the US, precisely meeting their demands.

Concrete Exchange proudly serves as the premier destination and partner for professionals across many industries, including decorative concrete, flatwork, resinous flooring, and painting contractors. Additionally, architects, interior designers, facility managers, and real estate investors rely on our comprehensive range of products and knowledge to achieve their goals.

Renowned for its distribution of leading brands such as SureCrete, Concrete Coatings, and Westcoat, among others, Concrete Exchange offers a comprehensive range of supplies for concrete coatings, restoration, resurfacing, and repair. Additionally, the company takes pride in its house brand, CX, which is a testament to its commitment to innovation and quality in the industry.

From concrete countertop materials to epoxies, urethanes, microcements, overlays, pigments, and stains, the company''s diverse inventory caters to a myriad of applications within the realm of concrete craftsmanship. Embracing both pros and DIY enthusiasts, Concrete Exchange provides seamless purchasing experiences and unparalleled customer service nationwide.

Concrete Exchange is proud to be recognized as a certified small business in California. This certification is a testament to our dedication to contributing positively to our local economy, fostering job creation, and supporting the economic fabric of our vibrant community. Beyond our roots and commitment to California, we are equally proud to be certified by the NGLCC as an LGBTQ-owned business. This distinction is more than a certification; it reflects our core values of diversity, inclusivity, and equality.', E'[''sports'', ''micro cements'', ''concrete wax'', ''concrete sealer'', ''concrete overlays'', ''concrete stains'', ''concrete countertops'', ''restaurant floors'', ''surecrete'', ''self leveling floor products'', ''pigments for concrete'', ''gfrc'', ''concrete coatings'', ''epoxy floor coatings'', ''subfloor preparation'', ''patio resurfacing'', ''metallic epoxy floors'', ''wooster paint rollers'', ''floor paint'', ''floor sealer'', ''stampible overlay'', ''decorative concretee'', ''sports teams'', ''australia'', ''professional'', ''major sporting events'', ''sporting stars'', ''building material'', ''manufacturing'', ''supply chain management'']', E'https://www.concreteexchange.com', E'2-10 employees', NULL, E'Concord, CA, United States', E'Concord', E'California', E'United States', E'[''925.240.3437'', ''800.877.6052'', ''+1 925 240 3437'', ''2008314'']', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, E'https://www.facebook.com/concreteexchange', E'https://www.twitter.com/chengconcrete', NULL, E'https://www.instagram.com/concreteexchange', E'7038269'),
